OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,FTotally Money said "millions" of
OL,7,Fpeople are out of contract with their
OL,8,Fmobile phone provider, and so also
OL,9,Ffree to leave and find a better deal `
OL,10,Fwith some SIM only deals available for
OL,11,Fless than #5 a month.
OL,13,FIn a sliver of good news, the price
OL,14,Fmost households pay for energy will
OL,15,Ffall by 7% from April 1, driven by
OL,16,Fpromised Government cuts to bills.
OL,26,@nD@TOUnD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
