OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,FOfgem's price cap will drop from the
OL,7,Fcurrent #1,758 to #1,641 ` a reduction
OL,8,Fof #117 or around #10 a month for the
OL,9,Faverage household using both
OL,10,Felectricity and gas.
OL,12,FHowever, the reduction is lower than
OL,13,Fthe average #150 cut to bills pledged
OL,14,Fby the Chancellor in November, when
OL,15,Fshe moved 75% of the cost of the
OL,16,Frenewables obligation from household
OL,17,Fbills onto general taxation and
OL,18,Fscrapped the energy company obligation
OL,19,F(Eco) scheme.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,FAnd of increasing concern is the
OL,7,Famount energy bills could rise by from
OL,8,FJuly as a result of the Middle East
OL,9,Fconflict, with latest predictions
OL,10,Fsuggesting this could be by well over
OL,11,F#300 a year.
OL,13,FIn the meantime, consumer groups have
OL,14,Furged households to send in meter
OL,15,Freadings ahead of April 1 to ensure
OL,16,Ftheir energy usage is billed at the
OL,17,Flowest possible rate, and investigate
OL,18,Ffixed rate deals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
