OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,FTotallyMoney spokesman James McCaffrey
OL,7,Fsaid: "With around 22 million
OL,8,Fhouseholds on their supplier's
OL,9,Fstandard variable rate, most are
OL,10,Fpaying the maximum allowed by the
OL,11,Fregulator.
OL,13,F"Check your current contract, and if
OL,14,Fyou haven't switched in the past year,
OL,15,Fit's likely you'll be free to leave `
OL,16,Fand you could save up to #917."
OL,26,@oD@GOUuD@AOUxD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,FHe added: "One in four broadband
OL,7,Fcustomers are out of contract, paying
OL,8,Fup to #9 per month more than those in
OL,9,Fcontract. To add salt to the wound,
OL,10,FBT, EE, Plusnet and Virgin Media are
OL,11,Fall hiking broadband prices by #4 a
OL,12,Fmonth, Sky by #3, and Vodafone by
OL,13,F#3.50 ` adding nearly #50 more per
OL,14,Fyear to bills.
OL,16,F"If you're out of contract, then
OL,17,Fyou're free to leave and find a better
OL,18,Fdeal. If you want to stay with your
OL,19,Fcurrent provider, pick up your phone
OL,20,Fand haggle for a new deal.
OL,26,@nD@KOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,F"They won't want to lose you to a
OL,7,Fcompetitor, and should offer you a
OL,8,Fbetter deal."
OL,10,FCitizens Advice chief executive Dame
OL,11,FClare Moriarty said: "Many households
OL,12,Fnever saw the back of the last cost-of-
OL,13,Fliving crisis, with millions of people
OL,14,Fstill unable to make ends meet.
OL,16,F"With key bills such as council tax
OL,17,Fand water rising from April and global
OL,18,Finstability threatening further price
OL,19,Fshocks, we're concerned about those
OL,20,Fwho have exhausted every option to
OL,21,Fkeep pace.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@MO]sD@VOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774929839
OL,3,CHouseholds braced for 'awful April' as
OL,4,Ccouncil tax and water bills soar
OL,6,F"So far this year, we're helping
OL,7,Fsomeone every 30 seconds with crisis
OL,8,Fsupport ` that's food bank referrals
OL,9,Fand charitable grants. And average
OL,10,Fdebt owed is hitting record levels.
OL,12,F"Those struggling most need a
OL,13,Flifeline. This should include better
OL,14,Ftargeted energy bill support for
OL,15,Fpeople on low incomes, help with
OL,16,Fsoaring rent costs, and support to
OL,17,Fhelp people get out of debt."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUyD@]O]
